data.name: Italian Meatball Burger
data.quickTastyDescription: Juicy meatballs topped with marinara and melty cheese, all packed in a toasted bun for a delightful twist on a classic burger.
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat your grill or skillet over medium heat.
In a large bowl, combine ground beef, breadcrumbs, egg, parsley, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and pepper. Mix until well combined.
Form the mixture into 4 equal-sized patties.
Heat olive oil in your skillet or grill. Cook the meatball patties for about 5-7 minutes on each side or until cooked through.
During the last minute of cooking, place a slice of mozzarella cheese on each patty and cover to melt.
Toast the burger buns on the grill or in a toaster until golden brown.
Assemble the burgers by placing a meatball patty on the bottom bun, topping with marinara sauce, and finishing with the top bun.
data.detailedName: Italian Meatball Burger with Marinara Sauce and Mozzarella
